description:
February 7th, 2024 will go down as one of the most important days of my life. It‚Äôs been nearly 7 years since I created this account as a way to express myself, vent about my job, and capture the absurdities of working on Wall Street / living in NYC as a mid-20s finance guy.

It‚Äôs been a long journey with many ups and downs, hard lessons learned along the way, and battles with anxiety, but I‚Äôm incredibly proud of what I‚Äôve built, where I stand today, and what the future has in store for me and the brand. What started out as a single meme page has since become a diversified holding company with a thriving newsletter @exec.sum, a portfolio of over 30+ startup investments, a recruiting firm @litneypartners, and a private members club @bondlifeclub (launching in East Hampton this summer).

While I would have loved to remain pseudonymous for much longer because I do not crave the spotlight, circumstances (that I will expand on later) made this the right time to take the mask off. I am glad to have revealed my identity and my story exclusively through the @financialtimes, one of the most respected news publications in the world. Thank you @madarbyshire for your professionalism and speed. 

My plan for social media is to continue posting memes, news, and everything that has made Litquidity what it is. My intention is not to start posting cringe reels and plastering my face everywhere. I still wish to remain relatively low key but I‚Äôm down to meet up with interesting people and explore potential business opportunities together.

Thank you all for the support over the past 7 years. I‚Äôm just getting started. Back to the memes ü§ù

(Photography by Alicia Vera/FT)
